The paper deals with feature extraction for action recognition, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed technique, Multi-skIp Feature Stacking (MIFS), involves enhancing features to improve their learnability, which is a topic of interest in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also evaluates the proposed method on several datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) research.
